{"id":"project-LICHEN-0bb7","title":"app_identity: copy_string calls strlen twice on same string","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_identity/app_identity.c:53-56

static int copy_string(char *dst, size_t dst_len, const char *src)
{
    ...
    if (strlen(src) >= dst_len) {     // Line 53
        return -ENAMETOOLONG;
    }
    memcpy(dst, src, strlen(src));    // Line 56
    return 0;
}

strlen(src) is computed twice. While src cannot change between calls (no aliasing concern), this is inefficient. On embedded systems with limited resources, unnecessary repeated strlen calls add up.

Suggested fix:
    size_t src_len = strlen(src);
    if (src_len >= dst_len) {
        return -ENAMETOOLONG;
    }
